  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add lamb shanks and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes. Remove and set aside.",
    "Reduce heat to medium and saut\u00119 onion until softened, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add garlic and saut\u00119 for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add canned tomatoes, lemon juice, honey, thyme, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Return lamb shanks to the pot and bring to a simmer.",
    "Cover and transfer to the preheated oven. Braise for 2 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender and falls off the bone.",
    "Remove from the oven and let rest for 10 minutes before serving.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley, if desired."
  ],
